        "content": "<p>Currently it seems that <code>norm_num</code> only handles division in division rings, excluding in particular <code>NNReal</code>?  In the following example, I needed an ad hoc application of a Mathlib lemma to close:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">NNReal</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NNReal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">div_lt_one_of_lt</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- necessary because `norm_num` does not work immediately</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Tactics such as <code>norm_cast</code>, <code>field_simp</code>, and <code>rify</code> also did not work here.</p>",
